reviews.review: The perfect encapsulation of the Skywalker Saga, this final movie does justice to the prequels and the original trilogy, all while concluding the sequels in a riveting and entertaining film.
JJ Abrams did a great job trying to fix the absolute disaster that The Last Jedi was and I would say it was a success.   The Rise of Skywalker puts the franchise back on solid ground.
Couldn't of asked for anything more. Great action and the storyline answers all your questions.

Inexcusably lazy writing that rushes to get from 'cool scene' to 'cool scene'. A horrible finale to what TFA had started, and a disservice to the other two trilogies. Simultaneously over, and under explains. Probably highly enjoyable if you detach it from the franchise and treat it as a 'shut your brain off' action movie.

This movie was complete and utter garbage.

Many theatregoers where I watched were heard saying "what?" and/or throwing their hands up and muttering "stupid" and other things.

Cannot blame JJ Abrams totally for this dumpster fire of a movie. A lot of the blame goes to Rian Johnson and Kathleen Kennedy.

They should keep their agenda politics out of of Star Wars or any other movies they are responsible for.
A fast paced and exciting conclusion to the Skywalker saga thats more fun than it should be. My personal favorite from the sequel trilogy.

Fresh new story. Shocking revelations were not really shocking, but kinda expected. J.J. learned from some mistakes with Force Awakens. Few parts I personally didn't like, but overall, good ending for this trilogy even though some things were left unanswered. I left the cinema with really mixed feelings, but after some procesing I came to conclusion that It did a really good job.

100% better than The Last Jedi, which was total garbage made by a person who obviously doesn't understand Star Wars at all.
With Rise of Skywalker, J.J. Abrams asks all of us to open our hearts and accept the joyful, innocent spirit of Star Wars once again.

Yes it was fan service, yes it had some questionable plot details.  Yes Lucasfilm messed up by not having an overarching plan for a trilogy of movies.  But this one was a lot of fun.  If you are looking for a perfect movie you aren't going to find it here.  Leave your brain at home, get that this is made for kids, and possibly folks that can just leave their brains at home, then you'll enjoy this.
